# 7. 中学時代の忘れ物

Honami: Okay, that should do it. This is more or less how most drum kits are set up.
Second-Year A: You need four cymbals...?
Honami: Drummers will change that depending on the song or their personal style.
First-Year A: S-Sorry, is there anything else that I should know?!
Honami: Hmm... Oh, you'll want to know how to tune them.
Honami: I'd like to hear for myself, so would it be alright if I played for a second...?
First-Year A: Yes, of course!
Honami: (It's been so long...)
Honami: (I think I still remember how to play the song we did all those years ago...)
First-Year B: Wow...!
First-Year A: Thank you for being such a great teacher, Mochizuki! I feel much more confident now!
Honami: You're welcome. Please let me know if you have any further questions.
First-Year B: You looked so cool playing just now! Did you use to be in a band or something?
Honami: Umm... For a little bit during elementary school. Oh, I also used to be a percussionist for the brass band.
First-Year B: Really...?!
First-Year A: Again, you were a lifesaver. I really can't thank you enough for what you did today!
Honami: Of course. Good luck during the school festival.
First-Year A: Thank you! Why don't we go turn in our application right now?
Second-Year A: Yeah, let's go!
Honami: That was the first time I played the drums in such a long time...
Honami: My hands and feet... No, my entire body still remembered what to do.
Honami: Including how to play that song.
Honami: I did join the brass band and keep practicing in secret after we called it quits. That may be why.
Honami: (I just remember how much fun I had while playing music as a group...)
Honami: (I wanted to become a better drummer and be the one to say, “Let's get our band back together.”)
Honami: (I kept practicing because I believed that day would come...)
Honami: (Unfortunately...)
Junior High Saki: Have you all decided which clubs you're gonna join?
Junior High Honami: I'll be continuing with brass band.
Junior High Shiho: I'm not joining one.
Junior High Ichika: I might not join one either...
Junior High Saki: Wait, but the choices are endless. Not joining a club seems like a huge waste.
Junior High Honami: While we're on the subject, Saki, you said you'd join a club once you were in junior high school, right? Do you know which one you're going to join?
Junior High Shiho: My guess is the home ec club. You get to have lots of snacks, right?
Junior High Saki: No! Drumroll, please...
Junior High Saki: I'm gonna join the soft tennis club!
Junior High Ichika, Honami & Shiho: What?!
Junior High Shiho: Are you serious? How are you gonna get through practice?
Junior High Saki: I'll be fine! The junior high and high school soft tennis clubs here are both supposed to be really laid-back.
Junior High Saki: I want to build my stamina up to the point that I don't have to take days off from school.
Junior High Saki: Then, we should be able to hang out a lot more than before♪
Junior High Honami: Saki...
Junior High Honami: Did you hear, Ichika?
Junior High Honami: For the very first time, Saki managed to keep up with everyone else in the club when they ran during practice yesterday. Also, she didn't make a single mistake while practicing serves.
Junior High Ichika: Yeah, I heard. I'm guessing she's probably telling Shiho right now.
Junior High Honami: She did seem really happy.
Junior High Honami: But it's also amazing...
Junior High Honami: When she first joined the soft tennis club, she had trouble doing half a lap around the schoolyard.
Junior High Ichika: The three of us even wondered if she'd be okay staying in the club.
Junior High Ichika: But...
Junior High Ichika: No matter how hard things get, Saki always seems to have a lot of fun...
Junior High Honami: *Nod*
Junior High Honami: She always had to sit off to the side during gym class in elementary school, so getting to move her body like this must be exhilarating for her.
Junior High Ichika: Yeah... Her eyes always twinkle whenever she talks about club stuff.
Junior High Ichika: I'm so glad that she's always smiling and laughing now.
Junior High Honami: Me too...
Junior High Honami: (It's really nice to see her enjoying club activities like this.)
Junior High Honami: (She's apparently even been staying late all by herself to work on her fundamentals recently.)
Junior High Honami: (She really must love getting to be in a club.)
Junior High Honami: (I've also become a much better drummer since entering junior high school, so I thought we could try playing together again...)
Junior High Honami: (But I suppose that can wait a little longer.)
Honami: Ultimately, I wasn't able to ask whether or not we could get our band back together...
Honami: (On the other hand, Saki's newfound stamina allowed the four of us to create some wonderful memories.)
Honami: (We were all in the same class during our first year, which allowed us to work together for both the sports festival and the school festival.)
Honami: (Ichika and Shiho were put in different classes during our second year...)
Honami: (But I did enjoy being teammates with Saki during the multi-class relay for the sports festival.)
Honami: (During our third year, Saki and I had to race against each other as the anchors for our respective classes. And she won by a nose.)
Honami: (I remember my classmates and I feeling so frustrated that time.)
Honami: (So, for the choir recital, we decided as a class that we'd outperform Saki's.)
Honami: (But the school trip is the source of our most precious memories...)
Honami: (I was so happy when I realized that Saki would finally get to go with us.)
Honami: (We had the second day to ourselves, so the four of us decided to see as many sights as we could. We even took quite a lot of pictures together.)
Honami: (All three years of junior high school were really fun...)
Honami: (I was hoping that we'd spend just as much time together in high school...)
Honami: (If this is the last time we're going to see each other on a regular basis...)
Honami: (I'd like to create one last memory with them.)
Honami: Am I the only one who feels this way...?
Honami: (I mean, the others are all so busy, and so am I.)
Honami: (So it probably won't be possible...)
Honami: It's okay... We don't have to get our band back together to make memories.
Honami: As long as we get to enjoy the school festival together, I'll be...
???: But it sounds like you already know what you want to do, Honami.
???: Why don't you just tell her that?
Honami: Huh...?
Honami: Did I imagine that just now?
Honami: Wait... I was going to return to class and help the others get ready for the school festival.
Honami: But they may've all gone home.
Honami: A notification? Oh, it's from that news app...
Honami: Oh...
Honami: That's right... It's almost that time of year.
Honami: I hope the skies are clear when the Leonid meteor shower appears.
